-- AIG Says Its Jet-Leasing Unit Owned Plane in Pakistan Crash Last Week
-- Susanna Ray
-- 2010-08-06T20:21:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/aig-leasing-unit-owned-plane-in-pakistan-crash-that-killed-all-152-aboard.html

          
          
             American International Group Inc.’s
plane-leasing unit owned the Airbus SAS jetliner that crashed
in Pakistan last week, killing all 152 on board, according to a
regulatory filing today.  
 AIG’s International Lease Finance Corp. spokesman Paul
Thibeau confirmed that the plane, leased by Airblue, was the one
referred to in today’s quarterly filing that discussed a July 28
accident.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Susanna Ray in Seattle at 
 sray7@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                                                 
                     
